{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"128c9e4f-f844-4c42-85ba-dc799c579fd1","content":"Here's what was migrated and how:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `<Property name=\"TestTimeout\" value=\"30000\" />` | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout></MSTest>` |\n| `<AssemblyResolution><TestDirectory useLoadContext=\"true\" />` | `<MSTest><DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled></MSTest>` (deployment is off by default in v3; the old load-context behavior is now standard) |\n| `<DataCollector>` under `<AgentRule>` | `<DataCollector>` under `<DataCollectionRunSettings>` (updated to v2.0 URI) |\n\n**Key points:**\n- The old `.testsettings` file can be deleted once you've verified the migration.\n- `RunSettingsFilePath` in the `.csproj` ensures `dotnet test` picks up the settings automatically (alternatively pass `--settings local.runsettings` on the CLI).\n- If you also need per-test timeouts, use `[Timeout(30000)]` on individual test methods.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cc15ff7e-7aa5-4976-aae0-c745efa2534a","outputTokens":277,"requestId":"2407:260E63:420EC8:46EDAD:6A031083"},"id":"fdc0ef0c-fd26-49c6-a9b3-c7b9d9c9b0da","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:35:41.151Z","parentId":"9f7d04c5-8387-44c8-aad6-800b0e4eda52"}
